## Activity Thresholds

| Status | Days Since Login | Action |
|--------|-----------------|--------|
| **Active** | < 30 | No action needed |
| **Stale** | 30 - 90 | Review access, confirm still needed |
| **Dormant** | > 90 | Revoke grants, disable user |
| **Never** | No login record | Investigate — pending onboarding or orphaned |

## Remediation Guide

### For Dormant Users
1. Revoke all role grants: `REVOKE ROLE <role> FROM USER <user>;`
2. Disable the user: `ALTER USER <user> SET DISABLED = TRUE;`
3. After 30-90 day retention period, drop: `DROP USER <user>;`

### For Unused Roles
1. Verify the role is not part of an active hierarchy (check Step 1.1 results)
2. Confirm no automated processes depend on the role
3. Drop the role: `DROP ROLE <role>;`

